		<div class="article FLC">
			<div class="sectionTitle FLC">
				<div class="difficulty"><span>Difficulty:</span> Easy</div>
				<h2 class="Heading1a Underline header"><span>Instructions</span></h2>
			</div>
			<!-- google_ad_section_start() -->
			
				<div class="thingsYouNeed">
					<h2 class="Heading5a">Things You'll Need:</h2>
					<ul>
						
							<li>
								<span>1/4 tsp cayenne  pepper</span>
							</li>
						
							<li>
								<span>1/4 tsp ground ginger</span>
							</li>
						
							<li>
								<span>1 T honey</span>
							</li>
						
							<li>
								<span>1 T apple cider vinegar</span>
							</li>
						
							<li>
								<span>2 T water</span>
							</li>
						
							<li>
								<span>small jar</span>
							</li>
						
					</ul>
				</div>
			
				<ol id='intelliTxt'>
					
							<li id="jsArticleStep1">
								<div class="stepNumber">1</div>
								
								<p>First you will need to wash out any small jar with soap and hot water. I used a small jam jar that I no longer needed. Dry it out with a paper towel.</p>
							</li>
						
							<li id="jsArticleStep2">
								<div class="stepNumber">2</div>
								
								<p>Now add all of the ingredients to the jar and shake well. Make sure the ingredients are well incorporated.</p>
							</li>
						
							<li id="jsArticleStep3">
								<div class="stepNumber">3</div>
								
								<p>Take 3 teaspoons of the syrup as needed for cough and/or irritated sore throat.</p>
							</li>
						
							<li id="jsArticleStep4">
								<div class="stepNumber">4</div>
								
								<p>Keep any unused portion in the refrigerater.</p>
							</li>
						
				</ol>
			
			<!-- google_ad_section_end() -->
