					I hate having to point this out all the time: 'Natural' ingredients absolutely can have side effects. All substances which have effects, cause those effects through a change in body chemistry. These changes can have the desired effect, such as reducing a headache, but this effect is caused by reduced swelling, which is in turn caused most commonly through the thinning of blood. Thinned blood means more bleeding in the event of a cut. This is a side effect.<br/><br/>Now, as for the concept of being 'natural', while true, it is also true of ALL medicine. Including over the counter expectorants. Yes they will contain flavors and dyes and such, but these flavors and dyes all come from natural sources. Not always the natural sources you'd like them to come from, but let's face it, you have no problem with bee vomit and rotten apple juice, so why squirm over crushed beetles for red dye.<br/><br/>There are...
				</p>
